714051f-a.title: Manhattan: 59th Street (West) - 10th Avenue
714051f-a.text:
West 59th Street, south side, east from Tenth Avenue,
showing details of the Roosevelt Hospital that occupies
the entire block to Ninth Avenue. The Nurses Home is at
Tenth Avenue; in the center is the Administration Bldg.;
at the corner of Ninth Avenue is the famous Syms Operating
Theatre. Across the glass enclosed roof of the latter,
appears portions of the massive American Women's Associa-
tion Club and Bldg. at 57th Street. To the left, above
the Ninth Avenue "El" station (demolished in January 1941)
are the towering apartment buildings on Central Park South.
April 15, 1939
No's. 1-2-3
P. L. Sperr
